731
00:29:39,237 --> 00:29:40,780
He left in quite
the hurry before.

732
00:29:41,531 --> 00:29:43,783
Think it was
something I said.

733
00:29:46,453 --> 00:29:48,371
I'm sorry.
Are you his latest, uh...?

734
00:29:48,538 --> 00:29:51,791
Trust me,
I'm not his latest anything.

735
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,042
All right.

736
00:29:54,961 --> 00:29:56,588
So, what <i>are</i> you
doing here, then?

737
00:29:56,796 --> 00:29:57,714
I'm having a bit of

738
00:29:57,922 --> 00:30:00,467
an existential crisis,
I suppose.

739
00:30:01,342 --> 00:30:03,178
I've been known
to be a good listener.

740
00:30:04,846 --> 00:30:05,472
Okay.

741
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,347
Uh...

742
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:09,392
I'm having some trouble
with my kids.

743
00:30:09,893 --> 00:30:11,478
Needed to get away from them
for a little bit?

744
00:30:11,978 --> 00:30:13,563
No, the opposite, actually.

745
00:30:14,814 --> 00:30:15,982
I'm trying
to get closer to them,

746
00:30:16,191 --> 00:30:18,067
but I'm not having much luck.

747
00:30:21,362 --> 00:30:22,197
Tell me.

748
00:30:23,490 --> 00:30:24,741
Are you a good son?

749
00:30:26,117 --> 00:30:27,368
I try to be.

750
00:30:28,411 --> 00:30:29,996
Well, then perhaps
you can explain.

751
00:30:31,664 --> 00:30:32,916
Would a good son

752
00:30:33,124 --> 00:30:36,878
blindly take his father's side
in a divorce?

753
00:30:39,088 --> 00:30:40,131
Would a good son

754
00:30:40,924 --> 00:30:42,342
send his mother to Hell?

755
00:30:44,552 --> 00:30:45,720
And would a good son

756
00:30:46,679 --> 00:30:48,681
stand here right before me,

757
00:30:49,098 --> 00:30:52,769
without a care in the world,
plotting to send me back?

758
00:30:56,022 --> 00:30:57,357
Mom?

759
00:30:59,108 --> 00:31:02,529
I thought I would come to Earth
to be with my sons.

760
00:31:03,696 --> 00:31:06,866
Instead, Lucifer is obsessed
with his human job,

761
00:31:07,283 --> 00:31:09,244
and you're still
your father's loyal soldier.

762
00:31:09,577 --> 00:31:12,956
I'm tired of fighting for things
that I'm never gonna have.

763
00:31:13,498 --> 00:31:16,376
So just take me back, Amenadiel.

764
00:31:16,584 --> 00:31:17,335
I'm ready.

765
00:31:19,546 --> 00:31:20,338
(sighs)

766
00:31:23,883 --> 00:31:25,009
(sniffles)

767
00:31:26,135 --> 00:31:27,679
No matter what happens,

768
00:31:28,429 --> 00:31:31,933
I will <i>always...</i> love you.

769
00:31:32,559 --> 00:31:33,476
Always.

770
00:31:35,603 --> 00:31:36,771
(sighs)

771
00:31:37,897 --> 00:31:38,898
Leila took down
both videos,

772
00:31:39,107 --> 00:31:40,567
killed Nick and Adam,
and then led us

