00:31:40,775 --> 00:31:42,527
by the nose until she
had time to escape.

774
00:31:43,319 --> 00:31:44,737
Why didn't I
realize it was her?

775
00:31:44,946 --> 00:31:46,030
Because as a punisher,
she's quite adept

776
00:31:46,239 --> 00:31:47,490
at avoiding
her own medicine.

777
00:31:48,157 --> 00:31:49,117
Quite impressed, really.

778
00:31:49,325 --> 00:31:50,326
(computer beeps)

779
00:31:53,872 --> 00:31:54,581
CHLOE:
Hey, Dan.

780
00:31:54,789 --> 00:31:56,749
Yeah, I just saw it.
I'm already working on a trace.

781
00:31:56,958 --> 00:31:58,167
LUCIFER:
"Judgment Day"? Oh.

782
00:31:58,376 --> 00:32:00,086
People should really be careful
how they use that phrase.

783
00:32:00,295 --> 00:32:02,255
It isn't actually due
for another couple of years.

784
00:32:02,922 --> 00:32:04,632
She's gonna kill herself
live on the air.

785
00:32:05,592 --> 00:32:07,886
What?
Well, that won't do at all.

786
00:32:08,094 --> 00:32:09,679
How am I supposed
to talk to her if she's dead?

787
00:32:09,888 --> 00:32:11,681
Glad you have
your priorities in order.

788
00:32:11,890 --> 00:32:13,808
Thought we were dealing with
someone smart and clever,

789
00:32:14,017 --> 00:32:15,768
who tortured with
a brutal sense of irony,

790
00:32:15,977 --> 00:32:16,769
but killing herself

791
00:32:16,978 --> 00:32:18,563
whilst humiliating
her company...

792
00:32:18,938 --> 00:32:20,315
Doesn't fit the pattern.

793
00:32:21,065 --> 00:32:23,651
Hey, Sharon, can you pull up the
video of Leila driving again?

794
00:32:23,860 --> 00:32:24,777
Yeah. Sure.

795
00:32:27,405 --> 00:32:28,364
Pause it there.

796
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:29,949
What are you
looking for, Detective?

797
00:32:30,158 --> 00:32:30,950
Zoom in

798
00:32:31,159 --> 00:32:32,201
to the edge of the seat.

799
00:32:33,453 --> 00:32:34,329
Can you go in tighter?

800
00:32:40,251 --> 00:32:41,711
Well, I know
images can be deceiving,

801
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,880
but that looks an awful lot
like a gun, doesn't it?

802
00:32:44,964 --> 00:32:46,215
CHLOE:
Leila's not our killer.

803
00:32:46,549 --> 00:32:47,634
She's in danger.

804
00:32:48,551 --> 00:32:49,886
You understand this
sicko pretty well.

805
00:32:50,094 --> 00:32:51,179
Where do you
think he's going?

806
00:32:51,888 --> 00:32:54,140
Well, somewhere linked
to her sins, I suppose.

807
00:32:54,974 --> 00:32:55,934
We barely know Leila.

808
00:32:56,142 --> 00:32:57,310
Who knows what the killer
thinks she's done?

809
00:32:57,685 --> 00:32:58,978
Well, she runs
the company that hosts

810
00:32:59,187 --> 00:33:01,356
humanity's worst depravities,
but we know she's not there.

811
00:33:02,065 --> 00:33:03,232
Hey, Dan,
how's the trace coming?

812
00:33:03,441 --> 00:33:05,652
The I.P. just keeps pinging
back to Wobble's main server.

813
00:33:05,860 --> 00:33:07,070
It's got to be
a mistake.

814
00:33:12,158 --> 00:33:14,035
Unless it's not
a mistake at all.

815
00:33:19,624 --> 00:33:21,084
You know, if you take
away the blinky lights

816
00:33:21,292 --> 00:33:22,168
and add some lost souls,

817
00:33:22,377 --> 00:33:24,671
this place bares a striking
resemblance to Hell.

818
00:33:25,296 --> 00:33:27,465
Shh. Listen.
(Leila speaking quietly)

819
00:33:27,674 --> 00:33:30,927
LEILA:
My name is... Leila Simms.

820
00:33:32,845 --> 00:33:34,764
I'm one of
the co-founders of Wobble.

821
00:33:36,557 --> 00:33:39,602
I wanted to apologize
to anybody who's watching

822
00:33:39,811 --> 00:33:42,897
for... for creating a forum...

823
00:33:44,691 --> 00:33:47,527
...where evil and hate
sought a refuge.

824
00:33:48,277 --> 00:33:50,571
And there's
Queen Wobble herself.

825
00:33:51,114 --> 00:33:52,573
Yeah, but where's
the killer?

826
00:33:53,032 --> 00:33:55,410
And tonight I go down
with the ship.

827
00:33:56,202 --> 00:33:56,995
(sobs softly)

828
00:33:57,203 --> 00:33:59,288
Right alongside
all of those awful sins

829
00:33:59,497 --> 00:34:02,667
that-that I helped
give a voice to.

830
00:34:03,251 --> 00:34:05,670
(crying) Please, please.

831
00:34:05,878 --> 00:34:07,880
P-Please, please.

832
00:34:08,464 --> 00:34:10,758
D-Don't make me do this.

833
00:34:10,967 --> 00:34:12,260
Please.

834
00:34:18,307 --> 00:34:19,475
(whispering):
There's Ray, the HR rep.

835
00:34:19,684 --> 00:34:22,770
Oh, goodness me,
I should have known.

836
00:34:22,979 --> 00:34:24,897
Halitosis--
first sign of evil.

837
00:34:25,106 --> 00:34:26,357
He had all the access
he needed

838
00:34:26,566 --> 00:34:28,943
to find his targets
and frame Leila.

839
00:34:33,197 --> 00:34:34,615
(sobs)

840
00:34:36,409 --> 00:34:38,119
What are you waiting for?
Shoot him.

841
00:34:38,494 --> 00:34:40,371
If he drops that lighter,
he'll kill her.

842
00:34:40,580 --> 00:34:41,956
I don't have a shot.

843
00:34:45,793 --> 00:34:48,880
(Leila crying softly)

844
00:34:56,095 --> 00:34:58,097
Okay, Detective, this next
part will be much easier

845
00:34:58,306 --> 00:35:00,558
if you're not here, so I'm gonna
politely ask you to leave, okay?

846
00:35:00,767 --> 00:35:01,768
I'm not going anywhere.

847
00:35:01,976 --> 00:35:04,187
We're gonna figure this out.
Just give me a second.

848
00:35:04,520 --> 00:35:05,438
(sighs)

849
00:35:05,646 --> 00:35:08,900
(Leila crying)

850
00:35:09,108 --> 00:35:10,902
All right, no rush.

851
00:35:11,861 --> 00:35:13,071
Whilst you're pondering,
I'm gonna go and have a word

852
00:35:13,279 --> 00:35:14,363
with our killer.

853
00:35:14,572 --> 00:35:15,490
That's a great idea.

854
00:35:17,075 --> 00:35:18,451
Sorry, say that again.

855
00:35:19,786 --> 00:35:22,163
I never meant to cause anybody
any pain.

856
00:35:24,123 --> 00:35:26,209
I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

857
00:35:26,417 --> 00:35:28,419
Yeah.
(whimpering)

858
00:35:29,170 --> 00:35:30,338
Hello, Raymond.

859
00:35:31,297 --> 00:35:33,466
Hate to, uh,
blow up your spot,

860
00:35:33,674 --> 00:35:35,343
but I have a question
to ask you before you complete

861
00:35:35,551 --> 00:35:37,428
this twisted little
mise-en-scene.

862
00:35:37,637 --> 00:35:38,513
Stay back.

863
00:35:38,721 --> 00:35:40,598
I swear I will drop this,
and she is dead.

864
00:35:40,807 --> 00:35:42,350
Oh, gosh,
there's the halitosis.

865
00:35:42,558 --> 00:35:43,434
It travels, doesn't it?

866
00:35:43,643 --> 00:35:45,520
You should really get that
looked at, but first,

867
00:35:46,270 --> 00:35:48,564
indulge me this one
simple query.

868
00:35:50,233 --> 00:35:50,858
Why?

869
00:35:54,529 --> 00:35:55,154
What?

870
00:35:55,530 --> 00:35:57,406
Why are you a punisher?

871
00:35:58,658 --> 00:36:00,535
I understand
the longing for justice

872
00:36:00,743 --> 00:36:02,703
or the joy
of sweet revenge,

873
00:36:03,162 --> 00:36:05,123
but no one's forcing you
to do this,

874
00:36:05,331 --> 00:36:07,875
so why would you
take it upon yourself?

875
00:36:10,753 --> 00:36:12,338
Because I couldn't
take it anymore.

876
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,298
All that evil

877
00:36:14,507 --> 00:36:15,383
is constantly spreading.

878
00:36:15,591 --> 00:36:16,676
I had to do something.

879
00:36:18,719 --> 00:36:20,304
I had to punish them.

880
00:36:21,681 --> 00:36:22,598
You're wrong.

881
00:36:24,058 --> 00:36:25,059
You didn't have
to do anything.

882
00:36:25,268 --> 00:36:26,519
You <i>wanted</i> to punish them.

883
00:36:26,978 --> 00:36:28,062
No, that's not true.

884
00:36:28,271 --> 00:36:30,398
Yes, it started with Nick--
that was impulsive.

885
00:36:30,606 --> 00:36:32,316
But then you got
a taste for blood,

886
00:36:32,525 --> 00:36:33,985
and it felt good, didn't it?

887
00:36:34,193 --> 00:36:35,194
I was doing my part.

888
00:36:35,403 --> 00:36:36,279
You had big plans

889
00:36:36,487 --> 00:36:37,613
to go on vengeance quest

890
00:36:37,822 --> 00:36:39,323
until we came
nipping at your heels,

891
00:36:39,532 --> 00:36:41,784
at which point
poor Leila took the fall.

892
00:36:41,993 --> 00:36:43,369
- An innocent!
- No, you're wrong.

893
00:36:43,578 --> 00:36:44,579
And then what,
you'd stop?

894
00:36:44,912 --> 00:36:46,497
Get away Scot-free?

895
00:36:46,706 --> 00:36:49,041
(chuckles)

896
00:36:49,250 --> 00:36:52,753
We both know you can't stop
because you love it!

897
00:36:53,212 --> 00:36:54,922
Just like the people
you punished.

898
00:36:55,131 --> 00:36:56,424
I don't! I...

899
00:37:01,345 --> 00:37:02,263
I do.

900
00:37:06,225 --> 00:37:09,562
I-I like seeing them
beg for forgiveness.

901
00:37:10,021 --> 00:37:11,647
You see, the difference
between us

902
00:37:12,690 --> 00:37:14,609
is that you became
part of the problem, Ray.

903
00:37:14,817 --> 00:37:17,361
Someone deserving
punishment.

904
00:37:19,822 --> 00:37:20,865
You're right.

905
00:37:23,576 --> 00:37:24,285
I do.

906
00:37:26,704 --> 00:37:27,705
We all do.

907
00:37:29,332 --> 00:37:30,666
No, wait!

908
00:37:34,462 --> 00:37:36,255
(fire alarm blaring)

909
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:45,473
(alarm stops)

910
00:37:49,227 --> 00:37:51,896
Man, you really don't shut up.

911
00:37:52,104 --> 00:37:53,689
Congratulations, Detective.

912
00:37:54,607 --> 00:37:56,776
I suppose you could say
I look quite extinguished.

913
00:37:58,277 --> 00:37:58,903
Right.

914
00:37:59,737 --> 00:38:00,821
Shall we get you untied?

915
00:38:04,784 --> 00:38:06,244
Burning the midnight oil?

916
00:38:07,036 --> 00:38:09,205
Ha, ha, what can I say?

917
00:38:09,830 --> 00:38:11,374
Being everybody's
bitch really sucks.

918
00:38:11,916 --> 00:38:13,417
Yeah, well,
it won't last forever.

919
00:38:14,835 --> 00:38:16,545
So I've had some time to think,

920
00:38:17,004 --> 00:38:20,299
and, um... I realize that

921
00:38:21,092 --> 00:38:22,218
I've been really harsh lately.

922
00:38:22,426 --> 00:38:23,094
It's okay...

923
00:38:23,302 --> 00:38:24,845
No, let me finish,
please.

924
00:38:25,513 --> 00:38:28,557
I've been really hard on you
for a while now.

925
00:38:28,849 --> 00:38:29,934
And I've been...

926
00:38:31,352 --> 00:38:33,396
so upset and so angry.

927
00:38:33,604 --> 00:38:37,400
And... I did,
I felt really betrayed.

928
00:38:38,067 --> 00:38:38,776
I know.

929
00:38:38,985 --> 00:38:40,861
But I realize you've...

930
00:38:41,612 --> 00:38:43,656
you've been working so hard
to make it right,

931
00:38:43,864 --> 00:38:47,159
and I feel like,
for the sake of Trixie,

932
00:38:47,368 --> 00:38:48,577
that we should go on the trip.

933
00:38:50,079 --> 00:38:50,955
You know, we should go,

934
00:38:51,163 --> 00:38:52,498
like we always have.

935
00:38:55,501 --> 00:38:56,585
I can't do that.

936
00:38:57,586 --> 00:38:59,046
Wh... What do you mean?

937
00:39:02,049 --> 00:39:03,301
You were right before.

938
00:39:05,553 --> 00:39:07,179
We shouldn't lie
to our daughter.

939
00:39:08,097 --> 00:39:08,806
Okay.

940
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:14,103
Look, I-I'm always gonna be
Trixie's dad.

941
00:39:16,355 --> 00:39:18,607
And I'm always gonna be
part of your lives.

942
00:39:19,650 --> 00:39:21,569
But we've been living
in the past for too long.

943
00:39:26,157 --> 00:39:27,450
We're no, we're no good
for Trixie

944
00:39:27,658 --> 00:39:29,285
if we're no good for each other.

945
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:35,916
But I think we both
know the truth.

946
00:39:41,839 --> 00:39:43,674
It's time we get a divorce.

947
00:39:55,019 --> 00:39:56,103
(elevator bell dings)

948
00:40:02,651 --> 00:40:03,778
Hello, Luci.

949
00:40:08,532 --> 00:40:09,867
Tell me you didn't do it.

950
00:40:10,868 --> 00:40:11,494
Do what?

951
00:40:11,702 --> 00:40:13,037
Don't play stupid with me.

952
00:40:13,245 --> 00:40:15,081
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

953
00:40:15,331 --> 00:40:16,832
Easy, Lucifer.

954
00:40:17,500 --> 00:40:18,793
Your brother didn't
send me to Hell,

955
00:40:19,001 --> 00:40:20,503
if that's what
you're worried about.

956
00:40:21,545 --> 00:40:23,714
But you were so adamant.

957
00:40:24,131 --> 00:40:25,383
I told you, Lucifer,

958
00:40:25,758 --> 00:40:27,760
a mother's love counts
for more than you think.

959
00:40:28,803 --> 00:40:30,346
My time on Earth
has helped me to realize

960
00:40:30,554 --> 00:40:33,099
that Father has a tendency
to overreact.

961
00:40:33,641 --> 00:40:35,434
So you're going
against Dad?

962
00:40:37,019 --> 00:40:39,021
Things change, brother.

963
00:40:39,688 --> 00:40:40,523
Do they?

964
00:40:42,024 --> 00:40:44,318
Well, I for one am grateful
that we're all just

965
00:40:44,652 --> 00:40:47,780
in the same room, together,
as a family again.

966
00:40:49,115 --> 00:40:50,366
Yes, not so fast, Mother.

967
00:40:51,158 --> 00:40:52,118
You see, I did
make a promise,

968
00:40:52,326 --> 00:40:53,994
and I am a man of my word.

969
00:40:54,620 --> 00:40:55,996
I told you that you
could stay here

970
00:40:56,205 --> 00:40:57,206
until I figured out how to

971
00:40:57,415 --> 00:40:59,125
reconcile my
deal with Dad,

972
00:40:59,333 --> 00:41:00,418
and now I have.

973
00:41:00,668 --> 00:41:02,628
So you're going to
punish me anyway?

974
00:41:02,837 --> 00:41:04,463
I am, indeed.
And not because

975
00:41:04,672 --> 00:41:07,466
I've been brainwashed by Dad
or I'm trying to prove anything.

976
00:41:07,675 --> 00:41:10,261
I punish because I'm good at it.

977
00:41:11,595 --> 00:41:13,431
I like giving people their due.

978
00:41:15,891 --> 00:41:16,684
Makes me happy.

979
00:41:17,977 --> 00:41:20,062
I suppose I can't ask
for a better reason.

980
00:41:20,312 --> 00:41:21,564
(scoffs softly)

981
00:41:22,148 --> 00:41:24,275
Which brings me
to your sentence.

982
00:41:26,902 --> 00:41:28,487
Mother... (inhales sharply)

983
00:41:28,696 --> 00:41:31,615
you shall remain
right here on Earth

984
00:41:31,824 --> 00:41:34,201
amongst the creatures
you so despise...

985
00:41:35,119 --> 00:41:35,870
as one of them.

986
00:41:36,871 --> 00:41:37,705
Wait.

987
00:41:38,456 --> 00:41:39,373
You're going to send me

988
00:41:39,582 --> 00:41:41,459
into the life of
Charlotte Richards?

989
00:41:42,042 --> 00:41:42,918
Mm-hmm.

990
00:41:43,169 --> 00:41:45,337
- Well, how's that
supposed to work?
- Not my problem.

991
00:41:45,754 --> 00:41:46,881
And what if I refuse?

992
00:41:47,298 --> 00:41:49,091
You can't fight this;
you're human now.

993
00:41:49,300 --> 00:41:50,468
But that husband...

994
00:41:50,676 --> 00:41:52,011
And there's children, right?

995
00:41:52,219 --> 00:41:53,554
They're going to <i>need</i> things.

996
00:41:53,762 --> 00:41:55,306
Oh, I'm counting on it.

997
00:41:55,973 --> 00:41:57,600
But if you truly want
to be with your sons,

998
00:41:57,808 --> 00:41:59,810
then that's the price
that you have to pay.

999
00:42:10,613 --> 00:42:11,989
So be it.

1000
00:42:28,547 --> 00:42:29,465
(gasps)

1001
00:42:29,673 --> 00:42:30,716
(grunting)

1002
00:42:31,133 --> 00:42:32,510
Your money or your life, bitch.

1003
00:42:33,010 --> 00:42:34,345
I-I choose money.

1004
00:42:36,388 --> 00:42:37,515
Does anyone choose life?

1005
00:42:37,723 --> 00:42:39,391
- That doesn't very...
- Come here!

1006
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:41,685
I'll give you what you want!
Just hold on.

1007
00:42:41,894 --> 00:42:43,646
I said, hold on!

